deaths_recoveries.notes: Died on 19th April. Was suffering from HTN.
Prominent Neuro surgeon of Chennai passed away at Apollo Hospital. Locals created ruckus and did not allow a proper burial fearing the disease.

The deceased who was suffering from Parkinson disease for the past three years was admitted to the hospital due to fever. His throat swab report arrived on Apr 20th night confirmed positive for coronavirus. He passed away in the morning of April 20th.
6 month old girl from Phagwara. Died at PGIMER Chandigarh. Tested positive on 21st Apr. Was in a hospital for over a month earlier in Ludhiana for a congenital heart problem.
P-432,History of Hypertension, Stroke and Pneumonia. Died on 23th Apr.
Was admitted to the SMS Hospital on April 22 and died on April 23. He was detected positive for COVID-19 on April 23. The patient had comorbidity of coronary artery disease.
Passed away on 22nd April at RGGH. Test results showed he was +ve for #Covid19.
From Madurai passed away on 24th April. She is the M/O one of the priests at Madurai Meenakshi temple.
Was brought dead to the SMS Hospital on April 22. As he was a suspected COVID-19 patient, a sample was taken which was reported positive on April 23.
Passed away on 25th April. Admitted to SKIMS Bemina on 13th April was suffering from HTN and other illnesses.
Passed away on the night of April 24th. Contract tracing suggests that he might have contracted the virus from Vegetable vendors who tested positive in Kundrathur
First policemen to die in Mumbai of Covid-19. He was a head constable at Vakola police station. He took ill on Apr 22 and communicated to his seniors. He passed away on Apr 25th.
Passed away in Kota on April 24 was found #COVID19 positive on April 25th. He had co-morbidity conditions of chronic renal failure and hypertension
Passed away on 25th April late night, suffered from cardiac issues. He was admitted to AIIMS on April 24 with a complaint of chest pain, fever and breathlessness.
She was suffering from diabetes, HTN and kidney disease.

KA-P465. She visited Moodalapalya maternity hospital complaining of bleeding. Was given medication and sent back. She returned later complaining of breathlessness and she was admitted to designated Covid-19 hospital on April 24th. She was moved to ICU on April 25th and she passed away on Apr 26th.
First doctor to pass away in WB. He was Assistant Director of Health Services. Was confirmed positive a week ago, his wife has also tested positive. He passed away on 26th April
Admitted to hospital on Apr 23rd. Had breathing problems and was put on ventilator. Died on Apr 26th.
